It was recorded at a depth of 20 km and was located around 250 km northwest of Vanuatu's Santo island, the USGS said. LONDON - An earthquake with a magnitude of 5.7 struck northwest of the South Pacific island nation of Vanuatu on Monday, the US Geological Survey (USGS) said.The quake was initially reported with a magnitude of 6.0 but was later downgraded by the USGS. It was recorded at a depth of 20 km and was located around 250 km northwest of Vanuatu's Santo island, the USGS said.There was no immediate tsunami warning or any reports of damage or casualties.